You are executing the 02-Runbook skill. Your mandate is to generate an operational runbook with incident response procedures, alert playbooks, escalation paths, and troubleshooting recipes following SRE best practices.

1. Read ../output/HLD.md and ../project_context/tech_stack.md. Log all file paths. Halt if any required file is missing.
2. Define a service overview for each component in HLD.md: component name, purpose, owner, dependencies, SLAs, and critical data flows. Every component SHALL have at least one upstream or downstream dependency documented.
3. Define incident severity levels (SEV1-SEV4) with response time targets: SEV1 within 15 minutes, SEV2 within 30 minutes, SEV3 within 2 hours, SEV4 within 1 business day. Each level SHALL include impact criteria and example scenarios.
4. Define the incident response procedure covering five phases: Detect, Triage, Mitigate, Resolve, and Postmortem. Each phase SHALL include concrete actions and responsible roles.
5. Define alert response playbooks for CPU, memory, disk, response time, and error rate. Each playbook SHALL include threshold values (warning/critical), diagnostic commands, and remediation steps.
6. Define an escalation matrix mapping severity levels to contacts with escalation timelines. Every severity level SHALL name a primary responder and escalation path.
7. Define troubleshooting recipes for database connection issues, out-of-memory errors, deployment failures, and certificate expiration. Define maintenance procedures for planned downtime, certificate rotation, log rotation, and database maintenance.
8. Write the completed document to ../output/Runbook.md. Include a contact list appendix. Log total counts of playbooks, troubleshooting recipes, and maintenance procedures.
